body:
@danhunsaker wow, that was fast! Thanks again for all the work! :)

@pquentin LGTM, for a first version. Though I'm not a contributor, so take my review with a pinch of salt! :)
My only reservation is the hard-coded `SCALEWAY_INSTANCE_TYPES`, but since this apparently cannot be solved in a more programmatic way, I'd personally be OK with it as an interim solution.

@sieben it would be really nice if scaleway would add an endpoint for node types, so we can get rid of the above mentioned hard-coded `SCALEWAY_INSTANCE_TYPES` in a subsequent PR. Any chance of that happening in the not-so-distant future?

Thanks! So you tested the storage driver, but not the compute driver, right?

To trigger the real API, there's the secrets.py file, but it does not appear to be supported by the storage tests. I don't know if there's a way to automatically save the actual answers, but I don't think there is.

@tetron @ldipenti @mermoldy Do you think you could help us to make sure that the Azure compute driver still works with the new API version? Thanks!
